      "title": "Goshuinchō (Cover)",
      "mapsUrl": null,
      "wikiUrl": null,
      "imageFile": "IMG_4069.jpg",
      "pageStyle": "cover",
      "commentary": "A <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shuin\">Goshuinchō</a> is a book that contains a collection of seal stamps from Japanese temples. Linh and Gary collected some of these stamps in 2011, and Linh collected the rest in 2017. At each temple, a monk stamped the book and then painted calligraphy. The pages of this companion app provide clear fonts in a similar layout to the calligraphy. Tap \"info\" at the bottom of each page to see translations. The text is read top-to-bottom, right-to-left.",
